The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | New Honda bike to hit the road
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      New Honda bike to hit the road
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Shinji Aoyama (centre) in New Delhi on Wednesday. Picture by Prem Singh                                  
	New Delhi, May 12: Honda Motorcycle amp; Scooter India is planning to roll out a new motorcycle this year that will compete with Hero Hondas premium 225cc Karizma.        
	We are set to launch a bike this fiscal. Our company has periodic meetings where we decide on our product line-up, Shinji Aoyama, president and CEO of Honda Motorcycle amp; Scooter India (HMSI), said. We are studying the possibility of a product in the Karizma segment, he told The Telegraph.         
	Hero Honda has been selling the Karizma since 2001. The company sells the 225cc Karizma at Rs 73,600, while the Karizma ZMR is priced at around Rs 92,500 (ex-showroom, Delhi).         
	HMSI today rolled out a new version of the 150cc Unicorn  CB Unicorn Dazzler. The bike is priced at Rs 62,900 (ex showroom Delhi). It will come with a five-speed transmission, Bharat Stage III emission compliant engine and give a mileage of 60 kms per litre.                                                                                                                                       
